{"questionId":"5123","questionHtml":"<p>Propene is reacted first with hydrogen chloride to produce X which is then reacted with aqueous sodium hydroxide to give Y. Finally, Y is reacted with excess acidified potassium dichromate solution.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><span class=\"mjpage mjpage__block\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"block\" alttext=\"{\\text{C}}{{\\text{H}}_{\\text{3}}}{\\text{CHC}}{{\\text{H}}_{\\text{2}}}\\xrightarrow{{{\\text{HCL}}}}{\\text{X}}\\xrightarrow{{{\\text{NaOH(aq)}}}}{\\text{Y}}\\xrightarrow{{{{\\text{H}}^ + }/{\\text{C}}{{\\text{r}}_2}{{\\text{O}}_7}^{2 - }{\\text{(aq)}}}}{\\text{Z}}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>C</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>H</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>3</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>CHC</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>H</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>2</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n  <mover>\n    <mo>→</mo>\n    <mpadded width=\"+0.611em\" lspace=\"0.278em\" voffset=\".15em\">\n      <mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <mtext>HCL</mtext>\n        </mrow>\n      </mrow>\n    </mpadded>\n  </mover>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>X</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mover>\n    <mo>→</mo>\n    <mpadded width=\"+0.611em\" lspace=\"0.278em\" voffset=\".15em\">\n      <mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <mtext>NaOH(aq)</mtext>\n        </mrow>\n      </mrow>\n    </mpadded>\n  </mover>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>Y</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mover>\n    <mo>→</mo>\n    <mpadded width=\"+0.611em\" lspace=\"0.278em\" voffset=\".15em\">\n      <mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <msup>\n            <mrow>\n              <mtext>H</mtext>\n            </mrow>\n            <mo>+</mo>\n          </msup>\n        </mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <mo>/</mo>\n        </mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <mtext>C</mtext>\n        </mrow>\n        <mro